3. Radians defining the chain

Radians convert arc geometry into linear relationships.

\theta = \frac{s}{r}

This is powerful because:
	•	rotations become linear variables
	•	oscillations become simple sine waves
	•	calculus becomes cleaner

So radians turn circular motion into something that can be handled like linear flow.

This is why radians appear in:
	•	Fourier analysis
	•	signal processing
	•	orbital mechanics
	•	quantum mechanics

They are essentially the bridge between rotation and linear math.

