A circle is actually just a slice of a higher-dimensional rotational system.

Examples:

Circle → rotation in 2D
Sphere → rotation in 3D
Hypersphere → rotation in higher dimensions

If you allow the radius to evolve while rotating, you get a spiral.

Example:

r = a e^{b\theta}

This produces a logarithmic spiral.

So:
	•	π controls the angular part
	•	e controls the growth rate

